Several lines on the incipit pages, alternating with black lines;
                                     numbers and titles of the psalms and of the
                                     canticles (spaces left for the titles of psalms have been left unfilled on ); incipits of the songs;
                                     the first refrain of each day of the Praise of Mary and the abbreviation standing for the refrain after the subsequential
                                     stanzas; holy names; names of the Hebrew letters in Ps. 118;
                                     the letters ስ and ብ in the word
                                     ስብሕዎ፡ at the beginning of each verse of Ps 150;
                                     the letters ይ and ር in the word
                                     ይባርክዎ፡ at the beginning of each line of the Third song of the Three Youths;
                                     elements of punctuation signs.
